        ax=plt.subplot(7,3,plotnumber)

    plotnumber+=1

In[55]:
for col in ['campaign','previous']:
    Q1=data[col].quantile(0.25)
    Q3=data[col].quantile(0.75)
    print(f"{col}")
    print("Q1 is ",Q1)
    print("Q3 is ",Q3)
    IQR=Q3-Q1
    print("IQR is " ,IQR)
    lower_limit= Q1-1.5*IQR
    upper_limit= Q3+1.5*IQR
    print("Lower_limit is " ,lower_limit)
    print("Upper_limit is ", upper_limit)
    data[col]=data[col].clip(lower_limit,upper_limit)

Task 3 Suggestions to Bank Marketing Team

# From your analysis 1. Increase marketing campaigns during economic downturns, as customers prefer safe investments at that time. 2. Re-target customers who were contacted in previous campaigns instead of focusing only on new customers. 3. Use the machine learning model (XGBoost) to shortlist high-potential customers before starting campaigns. 4. Optimize campaigns based on recall, not only accuracy, to ensure potential subscribers are not missed 5. Design targeted messages and offers for working-age customers rather than generic mass campaigns.

Final Model Selection

  1. XGBoost was chosen as the final model because it achieved the highest recall, allowing the bank to identify the maximum number of potential subscribers.
  2. The business objective focused on minimizing missed customers rather than maximizing accuracy, making recall a more important evaluation metric.
  3. Compared to other models, XGBoost successfully captured more positive cases, reducing the risk of losing interested customers.
  4. The model also maintained a good balance between precision and recall, as reflected by a strong F1-score.
  5. Models with higher accuracy such as Logistic Regression and Gradient Boosting were not selected due to their poor ability to detect actual subscribers.
  6. he final model selection supports a data-driven marketing strategy that improves campaign effectiveness and customer acquisition.

Challenges Faced

  1. Class imbalance solved using SMOTE & calss weighting
  2. High dimensionality handled via encoding
  3. Low recall initially improved using ensemble models
  4. Overfitting risk controlled using boosting parameters

Business Analytics

  1. Prioritize customers predicted as Yes
  2. Focus on customers with previous campaign success
  3. Reduce repeated calls
  4. Use model output before marketing calls
  5. Improve ROI and reduce cost
